Kaizer Chiefs founder and chairman Kaizer Motaung is locked in a bitter legal battle with the family's former lawyer after the sheriff attached R375,000 from his bank account in November last year using a subpoena issued by the South Gauteng high court. The attachment follows a default judgment granted against Motaung by the court on September 20 2018 for payment of the sum of R3 055 188 plus interest and legal costs. The bill was allegedly owed for legal services rendered to their son Kaizer Motaung Jnr. TO READ MORE ON THIS STORY GET A COPY OF TODAY'S SUNDAY WORLD